<subSubSection id="C3202CBBFFCAFFC87CFB8D86FC98F9B9" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B857F30FFCAFFC87CFB8D86FC98F9B9" blockId="52.[151,1436,1415,1628]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B94EA322FFCAFFC87CFB8D86FEF2FA44" bold="true" box="[151,275,1415,1441]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB02C1FFCAFFC87D708D89FE2EFA47" author="Schmid, F." box="[284,463,1416,1442]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref29667" refString="Schmid, F. (1958) Trichopteres de Ceylan. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, 54 (1 - 2), 1 - 173." type="journal article" year="1958">Schmid (1958)</bibRefCitation>
placed this species in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A04B3FFCAFFC87F608D89FC48FA44" box="[780,937,1416,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Nyctiophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94EA322FFCAFFC87F608D89FC48FA44" box="[780,937,1416,1441]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Nyctiophylax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with some hesitation due to its similarity with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A04B3FFCAFFC87CBA8DACFE95FA23" baseAuthorityName="Olah &amp; Johanson" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[214,372,1453,1478]" class="Insecta" family="Dipseudopsidae" genus="Hyalopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94EA322FFCAFFC87CBA8DACFE95FA23" box="[214,372,1453,1478]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Hyalopsyche</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol (1993) considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A04B3FFCAFFC87F898DACFB44FA23" authorityName="Ulmer" authorityYear="1930" box="[997,1189,1453,1478]" class="Insecta" family="Dipseudopsidae" genus="Hyalopsychella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94EA322FFCAFFC87F898DACFB44FA23" box="[997,1189,1453,1478]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Hyalopsychella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, now a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A04B3FFCAFFC87CFB8DD2FD8CFA09" authority="(Olah &amp; Johanson, 2009)" baseAuthorityName="Olah &amp; Johanson" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[151,621,1490,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Dipseudopsidae" genus="Hyalopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94EA322FFCAFFC87CFB8DD2FED0FA09" box="[151,305,1491,1516]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Hyalopsyche</emphasis>
(Oláh &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB02C1FFCAFFC87DCA8DD3FD84FA09" author="Johanson, K. A. &amp; Ward, J. B." box="[422,613,1490,1516]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="11 - 47" refId="ref28253" refString="Johanson, K. A. &amp; Ward, J. B. (2009) Description of twenty-one new Polyplectropus species from New Caledonia (Trichoptera: Polycentropodidae). Annales de la SociZtZ entomologique de France, 45 (1), 11 - 47." type="journal article" year="2009">Johanson, 2009</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, as a possible alternative genus for 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A04B3FFCAFFC878718DD2FE05F9F7" authority="Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol. However" authorityName="Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol. However" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Cyrnopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pingensis">
<emphasis id="B94EA322FFCAFFC878718DD2FAF1FA09" box="[1053,1296,1491,1516]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Cyrnopsis pingensis</emphasis>
Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol. However
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A04B3FFCAFFC87D838DF9FD03F9F7" box="[495,738,1528,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Dipseudopsidae" genus="Hyalopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B94EA322FFCAFFC87D838DF9FD67F9F4" box="[495,646,1528,1553]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Hyalopsyche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
have more complete venation, and are also the species with the simplest venation; the discoidal cell is closed in each hind wing; and the distance between the antennae is narrow in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A04B3FFCAFFC87D638E43FE2BF9B9" authorityName="Ulmer" authorityYear="1904" box="[271,458,1602,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Dipseudopsidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dipseudopsidae</taxonomicName>
but wide in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A04B3FFCAFFC87E318E42FC93F9B9" authorityName="Oláh &amp; Johanson" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Oláh &amp; Johanson" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[605,882,1603,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Cyrnopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hittigegamus">
<emphasis id="B94EA322FFCAFFC87E318E42FC93F9B9" box="[605,882,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Cyrnopsis hittigegamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
